  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Disaster Relief for Mudslide in Mocoa, Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On Saturday, April 1, while many families were asleep in their homes, a giant  wall of water, mud and debris from a horrific mudslide devastated the town of Mocoa in southern Colombia. Over 270 people are dead, with 400 injured and over 200 missing. Help us to bring urgent emergency relief of food, medicines, blankets, personal care and hygiene products and temporary housing,  and hope  to these communities as they begin to dig out from this awful tragedy</narrative>
  </description>
